==English==
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''[[fire]] [[and]] [[brimstone]]''' (''plural'': uncountable)
# the traditional [[punishment]]s of [[Hell]]
====Quotations====
*{{RQ:Authorized Version}} Revelations 14:10 ''and he shall be tormented with '''fire and brimstone''' in the presence of the holy angels, and in the presence of the Lamb''

===Adjective===
# referencing the power or [[wrath]] of [[God]]
#: ''That preacher gave a real '''fire and brimstone''' sermon!''
# {{pejorative}} Stereotypical descriptive for a [[charasmatic]] clergyman who stresses the power or wrath of God, [[literal]] [[interpretation]] of the [[Bible]] and traditional punishments of Hell.
#: ''The '''fire-and-brimstone''' preacher gave the city council a severe tounge-lashing after they voted on a zoning ordinance allowing a new strip club to open.''

